[The newswire reports detail the confusion surrounding how the product was
released with below-acceptable levels of Vitamin B1 (thiamine) for
infants. While there are infants that have to be fed infant formula, the
international effort "Breast is best" seems to be highlighted by this
incident. We await further information on the extent of this problem both
within Israel as well as internationally. - Mod.MPP]
